{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "This body of work underscores the importance of continuous monitoring and assessment of LLMs to understand and address their biases comprehensively.",
    "Bias Mitigation Strategies in LLMsThe pursuit of bias mitigation in LLMs has led to a diverse array of strategies, ranging from pre-processing and data augmentation to in-model adjustments and post-processing interventions [37]- [41].",
    "A significant research outcome has been the realization that no single strategy is universally effective, with the efficacy of different approaches varying based on the type of bias and the specific model [36], [42]- [44].",
    "Some studies have found that data augmentation, aimed at balancing underrepresented groups in the training data, can reduce certain biases without compromising model performance [45]- [47].",
    "Others have highlighted the potential of adversarial training and debiasing algorithms to make models less sensitive to biased inputs [5], [48]- [52]."
  ],
